<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="A" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Arras" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Arras,</orth> tapestry hangings of rooms, woven with figures: <bibl n="shak. cym 2.2.26" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. II, 2, 26</bibl>. Serving as a place of concealment: <bibl n="shak. wiv 3.3.97" default="NO" valid="yes">Wiv. III, 3, 97</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ado 1.3.63" default="NO" valid="yes">Ado I, 3, 63</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jn 4.1.2" default="NO" valid="yes">John IV, 1, 2</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h4 2.4.549" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A II, 4, 549</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h4 2.4.549" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A II, 4, 549</bibl> <bibl n="shak. 1h4 3.3.113" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 3, 113</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ham 2.2.163" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. II, 2, 163</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ham 3.3.28" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 3, 28</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ham 4.1.9" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 1, 9</bibl>. <emph>Arras counterpoints</emph> == counterpanes of tapestry, <bibl n="shak. shr 2.353" default="NO" valid="yes">Shr. II, 353</bibl>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>